dcterms:description: A multi-center cohort of 107,268 patients with a prior diagnosis of heart failure, collected from the electronic data warehouse of a large hospital network. The dataset includes patient trajectories over a maximum span of 40 years and a maximum number of 3,275 features, which includes labs, diagnoses, procedures, medications, tabular echocardiogram recordings, physical measurements, and admissions/discharges.
dcterms:title: Heart Failure Cohort

dcterms:creator: T. Chen
C. Guestrin
dcterms:description: XGBoost is a scalable tree boosting system that is widely used for classification and regression tasks with tabular datasets, and serves as a competitive baseline for time-series prediction tasks.
dcterms:title: XGBoost

dcterms:creator: M. N. Agrawal
H. Lang
M. Offin
L. Gazit
D. Sontag
dcterms:description: Order Contrastive Pretraining (OCP) leverages time irreversibility by taking two consecutive windows of data in their original temporal sequence to construct positive pairs, while negative pairs correspond to sequences where the temporal order is swapped.
dcterms:title: Order Contrastive Pretraining (OCP)

dcterms:creator: S. Tipirneni
C. K. Reddy
dcterms:description: Self-supervised Transformer for Time-Series (STraTS) is designed for handling sparse and irregularly sampled multivariate clinical time-series data, utilizing a transformer-based architecture for forecasting.
dcterms:title: Self-supervised Transformer for Time-Series (STraTS)

dcterms:description: Dual Event Time Transformer (DuETT) is designed for electronic health records, proposing a masked imputation pretraining task for detecting the presence of a feature and its value.
dcterms:title: Dual Event Time Transformer (DuETT)

dcterms:description: TCLR (Temporal Contrastive Learning for Video Representation) focuses on learning representations for video data through temporal contrastive learning.
dcterms:title: TCLR (Temporal Contrastive Learning for Video Representation)
